# Roadmap documentation hygiene

Apply this checklist when editing **roadmap-cluster** files (matched globs) or after **shipping / checking off** a pragmatic-phase item.

## Sources of truth

- **Checkboxes and priorities:** `docs/ROADMAP.md`
- **Phase definitions, gates, item ids (A–G, I, H):** `docs/ROADMAP_PRAGMATIC.md`
- **Navigation only (tables, links):** `docs/ROADMAP_MASTER.md` — must not contradict pragmatic; update when phases, ADRs, or major tiers change

## Link rules (files under `docs/`)

- **Wrong:** `[text](docs/FOO.md)` — resolves to `docs/docs/FOO.md`
- **Right:** `[FOO.md](FOO.md)` for same directory; code: `[lib.rs](../src/lib.rs)`; scripts: `[script.sh](../scripts/script.sh)`

## Naming (avoid collisions)

- **Phase G — G2** in `ROADMAP_PRAGMATIC.md` = TDA on blackboard traffic (research).
- **Transactional speculation backlog** = **ADR-001 follow-up**, not “ADR G2” or ambiguous “G2”.

## After substantive edits

1. **ROADMAP_MASTER:** Phase order **A–G, then I, then H**; gate summaries match pragmatic (e.g. Phase C = B3 **or** B4 **started**).
2. **README.md:** If you add a new roadmap-tier doc, add a row under “Start here” or “Roadmaps and plans”.
3. **ROADMAP_REMAINING_GAPS.md:** Bump **Last updated** when backlog/shipped tables change.
4. **ROADMAP.md ↔ ROADMAP_PRAGMATIC.md:** If you check a box in one, reconcile the other when they describe the same deliverable.

## Code ↔ docs (optional but high value)

If `speculative_execution`, `health_server` (`consciousness_dashboard.speculative_batch`), or `sandbox_tool` behavior changes, update **`docs/METRICS.md`** (§1b and related) and any ADR pointer in **`ROADMAP_REMAINING_GAPS.md`**.

## Chump / recurring pass

For a dedicated hygiene run, use **`docs/CURSOR_CLI_INTEGRATION.md`** § “Roadmap doc hygiene (recurring)” handoff text so Cursor loads this rule and runs the checklist without scope creep.
